  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Service Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Pest Pro is the modern pest control company. Through prevention, new technology and sustainable solutions, we meet the new demands for healthy environments, for both individuals and businesses.</strong></p><p><strong>Due to growth, we’re on the hunt for a highly ambitious Service Technician qualified in General Pest to join our team. As part of your role, you will be responsible for the below duties:</strong></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>To report to clients and conduct pest inspections and services</li><li>Determining the kind of treatment required to eliminate a particular type of pest</li><li>Identify pest infestation & carry out appropriate treatments for complaint area</li><li>Applying suitable pesticides to infested areas by following the label instructions and complying with safety procedures</li><li>Prepare daily reports, including records of equipment usage, work schedules and pest control operations performed</li><li>To maintain operation readiness for equipment and inventory</li><li>Supervise workers/ technicians for work schedules and responding to customers requests for various pest control services.</li></ul><p><strong>What we’re looking for:</strong></p><p><strong>Service Technician</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in pest control industry</li><li>Valid Class 3 / 3A License, NEA Full License</li><li>Positive and customer focused attitude</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul><li>Basic Salary $2,800 -$5,000 (OTE $33,600 - $60,000 P.A.)</li><li>Company vehicle + phone provided</li><li>Additional incentives</li><li>Commission on upsell opportunities you identify while at client sites</li><li>Opportunity for career progression, training, and development</li></ul><p><strong>If you would like to know more, apply today as we’d love to hear from you!</strong></p><p></p>",
